        "description": "The Rotaract Club of KSSEM proudly collaborated with RAC Delhi Pegasus and RAC VISTAS for the insightful session titled \u201cGlobal Skill Exchange Phase 3: Emotional Intelligence in Leadership\u201d, conducted virtually on April 4, 2026. The session featured Ms. Shikha Sharma, a distinguished Psychologist and Life Skill Educator, who delivered an engaging and thought-provoking workshop on the importance of emotional intelligence in effective leadership.\n\nRepresented by a dedicated delegation of six members, our club joined participants from various districts to explore how emotional intelligence (EQ) plays a vital role in team management, communication, and organizational growth. Through her expert guidance, Ms. Sharma introduced key psychological frameworks that emphasized empathy, self-awareness, conflict resolution, and inclusive leadership practices \u2014 all essential qualities within volunteer-driven organizations like Rotaract.\n\nThe session went beyond conventional leadership concepts by providing practical strategies to better understand interpersonal dynamics and make thoughtful, emotionally informed decisions. Our members gained valuable insights into maintaining team morale, fostering collaboration, and leading with both compassion and purpose.\n\nThe interactive Google Meet platform enabled a meaningful exchange of perspectives among participants, strengthening international connections and reinforcing the collaborative spirit of the global Rotaract network. This enriching experience not only fulfilled the collaboration criteria but also enhanced our club\u2019s leadership capacity by equipping members with the soft skills necessary to create lasting social impact. Inspired by the session, our delegation looks forward to implementing these empathetic leadership principles in future community initiatives and club activities.",
