        "areas_of_focus": "",
        "avenues_of_service": "",
        "description": "The Rotaract Club of Delhi Pegasus, RID 3012, in collaboration with the Rotaract Club of GHRSTU, RID 3030, successfully organized an insightful and engaging session titled \u201cThe Beauty Bloom\u201d on 25th March 2026 at 8:00 PM via Google Meet under the Professional Development Avenue.\nThe session featured Aayushi Mittal, Founder of Aayushi Mittal International Makeup Studio, as the esteemed guest speaker. She shared her inspiring journey in the makeup industry, offering valuable insights into building a successful career through passion, dedication, and continuous learning.\nThe session began with an introduction to the makeup industry, highlighting its vast scope and growing opportunities, especially in the coming years. Participants gained a deeper understanding of how the beauty industry is evolving and how aspiring artists can position themselves effectively in this competitive field.\nA key focus of the session was on entrepreneurship and personal branding. The speaker emphasized the importance of creating a unique identity, leveraging social media platforms, and maintaining consistency to attract and retain clients. She also shared practical strategies for beginners on how to build a strong portfolio, find initial clients, and gradually expand their network.\nAnother important takeaway was understanding common mistakes beginners should avoid, such as underpricing services, neglecting hygiene standards, and lacking confidence. The speaker encouraged participants to continuously upgrade their skills, invest in quality products, and stay updated with industry trends.\nThe session also covered essential skills required to become a successful makeup artist, including creativity, communication, professionalism, and adaptability. Additionally, participants were guided on how they can start their journey part-time and gradually transition into a full-time career.\nThe session was highly interactive, with participants actively engaging through questions and discussions. Queries related to career scope, client retention, pricing strategies, and certifications were thoughtfully addressed, making the session both informative and relatable.\nIn conclusion, \u201cThe Beauty Bloom\u201d proved to be an enriching and empowering experience that inspired participants to explore career opportunities in the makeup industry with confidence. The session successfully highlighted the blend of creativity, business acumen, and passion required to thrive in this field",
