        "description": "The Rotaract Club of KSSEM is proud to share that Rtr. Mahesh N, serving as the International Service Director, represented Rotary International District 3191 at Mahotsav 3.0: Dil Se Hyderabad, the Outgoing RIDE hosted by Rotaract District 3150 from 6th to 8th March 2026. He was accompanied by three other Rotaractors from District 3191, making it a valuable inter-district exchange experience.\n\nThe three-day event offered a perfect blend of cultural exposure and fellowship. The first day included a visit to the Statue of Equality, followed by an exploration of the historic Golconda Fort and an engaging laser show that highlighted its rich history. The second day featured a visit to the Salar Jung Museum, a boat ride to the Buddha Statue at Hussain Sagar, and a memorable double-decker bus ride along Necklace Road.\n\nThe final day covered key landmarks such as Birla Mandir, Chowmahalla Palace, and Charminar, showcasing the architectural and cultural heritage of Hyderabad. Beyond the sightseeing, the warmth and hospitality extended by the host district stood out, with thoughtful gestures like handwritten notes adding a personal touch to the experience.\n\nMahotsav 3.0 served as a platform for strengthening inter-district relations, fostering cultural exchange, and building meaningful connections. The club takes pride in this representation and the valuable experiences gained through this international service initiative.",
