        "description": "The Rotaract Club of Delhi Pegasus, RID 3012, in collaboration with Elysium \u2013 The District Mental Health Team, successfully organized an insightful session titled \u201cPeace Begins in Behaviour\u201d under the Rotary Focus Area of Peace Building & Conflict Resolution on 25th February 2026 from 7:00 PM to 8:00 PM via Google Meet.\nThe session was conducted by Snehal Gautam, an Organizational Psychologist, who delivered a thoughtful and engaging presentation on understanding conflict, improving communication, and fostering peaceful interactions in everyday life. The session aimed to help participants recognize how individual behaviour and emotional awareness play a crucial role in resolving conflicts and building harmonious relationships.\nDuring the session, Snehal Gautam emphasized that peace is not the absence of conflict but the ability to handle conflicts constructively. She introduced participants to different ways individuals respond during conflicts, such as avoiding the situation, confronting it immediately, overthinking privately, or trying to resolve it for everyone. Through this, participants were encouraged to reflect on their own conflict-handling styles.\nA key highlight of the session was the discussion on Active Listening and Reflective Listening. Participants learned how active listening focuses on understanding the words being spoken, while reflective listening goes deeper by recognizing the emotions behind those words. Snehal explained how responding with empathy and curiosity instead of judgment can significantly improve communication and relationships.\nThe session also explored the importance of shifting from judgmental thinking to curiosity and empathy. Through relatable examples, participants were encouraged to understand that people may behave differently due to their emotions, perspectives, or circumstances, and approaching situations with empathy can lead to more peaceful resolutions.\nThe interactive nature of the session encouraged participants to reflect on their own behaviour patterns, communication styles, and reactions during conflicts. Attendees actively engaged in discussions and gained practical insights on how to apply these concepts in personal relationships, teamwork, and leadership roles.\nOverall, \u201cPeace Begins in Behaviour\u201d proved to be a meaningful and impactful session that inspired participants to practice empathy, listen more mindfully, and approach conflicts with understanding and emotional intelligence, thereby contributing to a more peaceful and supportive environment.",
