        "description": "The Rotaract Club of Mount Carmel College organized an impactful online session titled \u201cBreaking the Silence: Mental Health at Work\u201d on 23rd December, conducted via Google Meet from 6:00 PM to 7:00 PM. The session aimed to create awareness about mental health in professional environments and encourage open conversations around emotional well-being.\n\nThe session was led by Mr. Anmol Sanghai, who delivered an insightful and thoughtful discussion on the importance of mental health in the workplace. He addressed common challenges such as stress, burnout, emotional pressure, and the stigma often associated with mental health concerns. Through clear explanations and relatable examples, the speaker emphasized the need for emotional resilience, self-care, and supportive work cultures.\n\nParticipants gained a better understanding of how mental health directly impacts productivity, relationships, and overall job satisfaction. The session highlighted practical ways to recognize mental health concerns, manage stress effectively, and maintain a healthy work-life balance. The speaker also encouraged participants to seek help when needed and to support others by fostering empathy and understanding in professional spaces.\n\nThe event was conducted as a collaborative initiative, with a requirement of five members per participating club. E-certificates were provided to all registered participants. The session was well-received and appreciated for its relevance, clarity, and meaningful message.\n\nOverall, Breaking the Silence served as an important step toward promoting mental health awareness and reinforcing the value of emotional well-being in today\u2019s fast-paced work environment.",
