        "end_date": "21/12/2025",
        "areas_of_focus": "Growing Local Economies, Supporting Education",
        "avenues_of_service": "Public Image, Community Service",
        "description": "\u0cac\u0cc6\u0cb3\u0c95\u0cc1 was a heartfelt community service initiative carried out in collaboration with Rotary District 3191, symbolizing hope, care, and sustainable living. Through this project, our club took a meaningful step toward supporting underprivileged families by distributing 18 solar lamps to needy households in nearby slum areas.\n\nThe initiative aimed not only to provide light but also to bring safety, comfort, and dignity into the everyday lives of the beneficiaries. Each solar lamp distributed under \u0cac\u0cc6\u0cb3\u0c95\u0cc1 operates using the power of sunlight. During the daytime, the lamps charge naturally, and at night they provide bright, reliable illumination without the need for electricity. This made them especially valuable for families with limited or no access to a stable power supply. The lamps are eco-friendly, cost-effective, and easy to use, making them a sustainable solution for daily living.\n\nAlong with the distribution, our team, along with the support of District 3191, patiently explained how to use and maintain the solar lamps to every family. The beneficiaries were guided on proper charging, usage hours, and basic care, ensuring that the lamps could be used effectively for a long period. Special attention was given to elderly members and children so that everyone could confidently operate the lamps.\n\nThe smiles and gratitude of the 20 families clearly reflected the impact of this initiative. For many homes, these lamps meant safer nights, better visibility for children to study, and relief from darkness.\n\n\u0cac\u0cc6\u0cb3\u0c95\u0cc1 was more than just a solar lamp distribution drive; it was a reminder that small actions, when supported through meaningful collaboration, can create lasting change. By lighting homes, we also lit hearts\u2014reinforcing our commitment to service, sustainability, and social responsibility.",
