        "description": "The webinar titled \u201cSilent Scars: Impact of Sexual Abuse on Mental Health\u201d was thoughtfully organized by the Rotaract Club of Young Visionaries on 15th November 2025 at 7:00 PM via Google Meet. The session aimed to spread awareness, empathy, and understanding about the long-term psychological effects of sexual abuse, while creating a safe and sensitive space for learning.\n\nThe resource person for the event, Ms. Malika Narang, a Mental Health Advocate and Psychologist, shared deep insights into the emotional and psychological aftermath that survivors often experience, including anxiety, fear, guilt, and trust issues. She emphasized the importance of acknowledging survivors\u2019 experiences, validating their feelings, and avoiding victim-blaming. The session also highlighted healthy coping mechanisms, the role of therapy, and the importance of timely psychological support in the healing journey.\n\nParticipants were guided on how to respond sensitively to survivors, listen without judgment, and encourage professional help when needed. The session stressed building a more compassionate and informed society where survivors feel seen, heard, and supported.\n\nThe event saw active participation from various clubs that met the collaboration criteria of a minimum of five members. Under the leadership of Rtr. Priyanka Bose (President), Rtr. Mehak Sharma (Vocational Services Director), and Rtr. Muskan (Event Chair), the webinar proved to be impactful, informative, and emotionally resonant.",
