        "description": "The Be the Reason online awareness session, organized under Project Snehdhara by the Rotaract Club of Delhi South Central, sponsored by the Rotary Club of Delhi South Central, was successfully conducted on 18th October 2025 at 8:00 PM via Google Meet. The session aimed to promote awareness about blood, eye, and organ donation, inspiring participants to understand the power of giving and the profound impact it can have on saving lives.\n\nThe esteemed speaker for the event, Dr. Anuj Gaba (MD, Resident in Forensic Medicine and Toxicology, AIIMS Kalyani), shared insightful knowledge about the importance, safety, and process of donations. He emphasized how every donor holds the power to bring hope and a new beginning to others, dispelling myths and encouraging participants to take meaningful steps toward contributing to this noble cause.\n\nThe event witnessed enthusiastic participation from several Rotaract clubs, meeting the collaboration criteria of at least five members per club. Participants appreciated the informative and empathetic tone of the session, which not only educated but also inspired them to take part in life-saving initiatives.\n\nUnder the guidance of Rtr. Isha Parashar (Project Chair), Rtr. Sukhmani Kaur (Event Chair), Rtr. Manthan Mangla (Event Co-Chair), Rtr. Priyanshu Sharma (President), and Rtr. Jasleen Johar (Secretary), the session concluded as a heartwarming and impactful effort toward spreading compassion and awareness about the gift of life.",
