        "description": "The ADHIKAR \u2013 Multi-District Open Panel Discussion on Voting Awareness was successfully organized by the Rotaract Club of JIT, RID 3030 on 18th October 2025 from 7:00 PM to 8:00 PM via an online platform. Conducted under District 3030\u2019s initiative \u2013 Project Adhikar, the event focused on raising awareness about the importance of voting and encouraging youth to take an active role in the democratic process.\n\nThe panel discussion provided an engaging platform for participants to understand the significance of every vote and the responsibility that comes with it. The speakers shed light on topics such as voter education, the impact of informed decision-making, and the power of collective participation in shaping the nation\u2019s future. Discussions also highlighted the role of youth in strengthening democracy and promoting civic responsibility.\n\nThe event witnessed enthusiastic participation from multiple Rotaract clubs across districts, fulfilling the collaboration requirement of at least five members per club. Participants found the session thought-provoking and inspiring, appreciating the initiative for promoting awareness about their fundamental right \u2014 the right to vote.\n\nThe session concluded successfully under the leadership of Rtr. Grisha Kingrani (President), Rtr. Parineeta Kapse (Event Chair), and Rtr. Yash Tanwani (Event Chair), marking a meaningful step toward youth empowerment and active\u00a0citizenship.",
