        "description": "The SpeakEasy: From Nervous to Noteworthy online public speaking session, organized by the Rotaract Club of Bangalore West, was successfully conducted on 17th October 2025 at 7:00 PM onwards. The session aimed to help participants overcome stage fright, develop confidence, and enhance their communication skills to express themselves effectively and impactfully.\n\nThe session was led by Ms. Hemalatha, who shared valuable insights on how to transform nervousness into confidence while speaking in front of an audience. She discussed key aspects of public speaking such as clarity, body language, tone modulation, and audience engagement. Through practical tips and interactive examples, participants learned how to structure their thoughts, speak naturally, and make a lasting impression.\n\nThe event saw active participation from both community-based and institution-based clubs, meeting the collaboration criteria of a minimum of five and ten members respectively. Non-Rotaractors also participated enthusiastically, making the session diverse and engaging.\n\nThe participants appreciated the speaker\u2019s approachable style and the session\u2019s practical focus, which made the learning experience both inspiring and enjoyable. The event concluded with appreciation for the organizing team \u2014 Rtr. Shankar Prabhudev (President), Rtr. Sansita Rao (Secretary), Rtr. Lakshmi S Iyengar, and Rtr. Dhruti V Wadki (Professional Development Directors) \u2014 for delivering an empowering and confidence-boosting session.",
