        "avenues_of_service": "Public Image, Community Service",
        "description": "The Small Act, Big Impact online session organized by the Rotaract Club of YCCE, RID 3030 was successfully conducted on 7th October 2025 at 7 PM via Google Meet. The session aimed to raise awareness about how small, conscious actions in daily life can collectively create a significant positive impact on the environment and society.\n\nThe event featured engaging discussions on sustainable practices and practical steps to reduce environmental harm. Participants explored the environmental impact chain, learning how simple actions like fixing a leaking tap, using leftover water for plants, or reducing single-use plastics can contribute to resource conservation. The session also included myth-busting segments, such as clarifying that biodegradable products do not always decompose quickly in landfills, encouraging participants to adopt more informed and responsible habits.\n\nThe interactive format allowed participants to share ideas and ask questions, making the session highly engaging and informative. The collaboration form encouraged clubs to join with a minimum of five members, fostering teamwork and collective learning. Participants expressed appreciation for the actionable insights provided, emphasizing that even small individual efforts can lead to meaningful change when applied consistently.\n\nThe event concluded with gratitude from the organizing team  Rtr. Tejasvi Jadhao (International Service Director) and Rtr. Pranav Kakde (Event Chair) marking it as a successful initiative in promoting environmental responsibility and social impact.",
