        "description": "The Rotaract Club of KSSEM organized a professional development event titled \u201cCrack the Code: Interview Edition\u201d on 23rd September 2025 at 6:30 PM. The session aimed to equip students with valuable insights into campus placements and interview preparation through firsthand experiences shared by the club\u2019s 7th-semester seniors who recently secured placements.\nThe event featured a panel of accomplished speakers who shared their personal journeys, preparation techniques, and strategies for excelling in both technical and HR interview rounds. They offered practical advice on communication, confidence-building, and handling challenging interview questions, giving participants a real-world understanding of the placement process.\nThe session drew an enthusiastic audience with active participation and engaging discussions. Students interacted freely with the speakers, asking questions about company expectations, technical assessments, and effective preparation methods.\nThe event was conducted exclusively for 100 participants, creating a focused and interactive learning environment. Through this initiative, the Rotaract Club of KSSEM successfully provided a platform for peer learning and professional growth, empowering students to approach their future interviews with greater clarity and confidence.\n\u201cCrack the Code: Interview Edition\u201d stood out as an inspiring and informative session, bridging the gap between academic learning and professional readiness, and reflecting the club\u2019s ongoing commitment to personal and professional development among its members.\n",
